<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="731" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1127,786,1580]" box="[151,827,878,908]" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,290,883,907]" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">Description.</emphasis>
Body length: ♂♂ 
<quantity box="[486,613,883,907]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.1" metricValueMax="9.5" metricValueMin="8.7" pageId="16" pageNumber="731" unit="mm" value="9.1" valueMax="9.5" valueMin="8.7">8.7–9.5 mm</quantity>
(
<typeStatus box="[628,723,883,907]" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity box="[729,815,883,908]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="731" unit="mm" value="9.5">9.5 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1127,786,1580]" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">
Male (
<typeStatus box="[252,350,915,939]" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<figureCitation box="[363,444,915,939]" captionStart="Figs 52–55" captionStartId="21.[113,150,1511,1530]" captionTargetBox="[170,1033,222,1469]" captionTargetId="figure-14@21.[163,1040,218,1474]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 52–55. Habitus. 52 – Hesperopenna bonifaci sp. nov. (male, holotype, 9.5 mm); 53 – H. helferi sp. nov. (male, paratype, 8.5 mm); 54 – H. sipekorum sp. nov. (male, holotype, 8.6 mm); 55 – H. zofka sp. nov. (male, holotype, 6.9 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5740065/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
). Body completely orange brown, apical half of elytra slightly paler, apices of mandibles black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1127,786,1580]" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">
Interocular space 1.6 times as wide as transverse diameter of eye. Antennae 0.85 times as long as body, length ratio of antennomeres I to XI equals 19-5-8-18-18-18-18-17-17-15- 17. Pronotum 1.55 times as broad as long. Elytra glabrous (only several pale setae on apical slopes), 1.85 times as long as wide (measured at humeral calli), 0.75 times as long as body. Length ratio of metatarsomeres I–IV equals 14-7-5-12. Last ventrite posteriorly with two small incisions (
<figureCitation box="[325,405,1139,1164]" captionStart="Figs 19–26" captionStartId="15.[112,149,1058,1077]" captionTargetBox="[124,1078,218,1029]" captionTargetId="figure-153@15.[113,1088,207,1034]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 19–26. Last abdominal ventrite of males.19 – Hesperopenna medvedevi nom. nov.; 20 – H. persimilis (Kimoto, 1989); 21 – H. tibialis (Kimoto, 1989); 22 – H. arnoldi sp. nov.; 23 – H. bonifaci sp. nov.; 24 – H. helferi sp. nov.; 25 – H. sipekorum sp. nov.; 26 – H. zofka sp. nov. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5740049/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1127,786,1580]" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">
Aedeagus: dorsal side medially with very long thin incision, apically pointed to two touching processes; ventral side apically asymmetrical, on left with U-shaped incision, on right with short process with rounded apex (
<figureCitation box="[511,590,1235,1259]" captionStart="Figs 15–18" captionStartId="13.[115,152,1542,1561]" captionTargetBox="[126,1079,226,1362]" captionTargetId="figure-14@13.[113,1090,218,1370]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 15–18. Aedeagus (a – dorsal view; b – lateral view; c – ventral view). 15 – H. bonifaci sp. nov.; 16 – H. helferi sp. nov.; 17 – H. sipekorum sp. nov.; 18 – H. zofka sp. nov. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5740045/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1127,786,1580]" box="[181,373,1267,1291]" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">Female unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1127,786,1580]" box="[181,848,1299,1324]" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">
Variability. In 
<typeStatus box="[335,430,1300,1324]" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">paratype</typeStatus>
, pronotum 1.45 times as broad as long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="731" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1127,786,1580]" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,402,1331,1355]" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Having glabrous elytra and brown legs, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezděk, 2013" authorityName="Bezděk" authorityYear="2013" box="[840,1088,1333,1356]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hesperopenna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="731" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bonifaci" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[840,1088,1333,1356]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">Hesperopenna bonifaci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="16" pageNumber="731" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezděk, 2013" authorityName="Bezděk" authorityYear="2013" box="[343,448,1365,1388]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hesperopenna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="731" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helferi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[343,448,1365,1388]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">H. helferi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[456,541,1364,1387]" pageId="16" pageNumber="731" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Both species can be distinguished by the structure of aedeagus which in 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezděk, 2013" authorityName="Bezděk" authorityYear="2013" box="[361,482,1397,1420]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hesperopenna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="731" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bonifaci" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[361,482,1397,1420]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">H. bonifaci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[492,576,1396,1419]" pageId="16" pageNumber="731" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
forms two thin touching processes dorsally and is deeply incised on the left side ventrally, while in 
<taxonomicName authority="Bezděk, 2013" authorityName="Bezděk" authorityYear="2013" box="[658,757,1429,1452]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hesperopenna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="731" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helferi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[658,757,1429,1452]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">H. helferi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[763,843,1428,1451]" pageId="16" pageNumber="731" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
forms two wider processes dorsally and is deeply incised on the right side ventrally, moreover with a high median keel (
<figureCitation box="[159,283,1491,1515]" captionStart="Figs 15–18" captionStartId="13.[115,152,1542,1561]" captionTargetBox="[126,1079,226,1362]" captionTargetId="figure-14@13.[113,1090,218,1370]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 15–18. Aedeagus (a – dorsal view; b – lateral view; c – ventral view). 15 – H. bonifaci sp. nov.; 16 – H. helferi sp. nov.; 17 – H. sipekorum sp. nov.; 18 – H. zofka sp. nov. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5740045/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="731">Figs 15, 16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[151,1070,1523,1548]" pageId="16" pageNumber="731" type="etymology">
